snippet.textDisplay:
Fun story about cheese making:
I was in a microbiology class and we were making cheese for one of our projects (and then making pizza with said cheese cause science!) The cheese had to sit in a refrigerator over two days in order to congeal, so we all piled our cheese cloths in the fridge and left. THE VERY NEXT DAY we walk back into class and our teacher announced that someone had left the fridge open, she wouldn’t name names (Chris), and all the cheese was spoiled. Needless to say, the class was upset as well as the teacher who claimed this was the first time something like this had happened. We still made pizza, but we had to use store bought cheese, so the pizza was bittersweet...that or I made my dough wrong, either or.
